        "full_description": "Ekadashi, 20 December 2026\n\nMokshada Ekadashi falls during the waxing moon in November-December. Its glory is described in the Brahmanda Purana in a conversation between Lord Krishna and Maharaja Yudhishthira.\n\nYudhishthira once asked Lord Krishna: \"My dear Krishna, what is the name of the Ekadashi that comes during the waxing moon in November-December? Please also describe the proper observance of this Ekadashi.\"\n\nLord Krishna replied: \"O best of kings, this Ekadashi destroys the reactions of sinful actions. If on this day one worships the Supreme Lord with tulasi manjaris, the Lord becomes very pleased. By observing this Ekadashi one receives the result of performing a Vajapeya sacrifice.\"\n\nIn ancient times there was a king named Vaikhanasa who ruled the city of Champaka. He was kind to his subjects, and many learned brahmanas lived in his kingdom. One night the king dreamed that his father had fallen into hell and was suffering terribly. Deeply disturbed, the king told the brahmanas about the dream the next day.\n\nIn the dream, his father begged to be delivered from hell. From that time the king lost all peace. He found no taste in royal power, wealth, family life, or state affairs. He thought that all his prosperity was useless if his father was suffering. In distress he asked the learned brahmanas: \"Please tell me how I can rescue my father from hell.\"\n\nThe brahmanas replied: \"O king, the ashram of Parvata Muni is nearby. He knows past, present, and future. Go to him and explain your dream.\" Following their advice, King Vaikhanasa went to the sage with the brahmanas and his subjects.\n\nWhen Parvata Muni asked about the welfare of the kingdom, the king answered: \"By your mercy we are all well, but I am suffering greatly. Although I have a kingdom and every kind of wealth, doubts and pain fill my mind.\" He then described the dream.\n\nParvata Muni entered meditation. After some time he said: \"My dear king, in a previous life your father was overcome by lust, and for that reason he is now suffering in hell. You should observe the Ekadashi vow during the waxing moon in November-December and offer the merit of that observance to your father. By the power of your piety he will be delivered.\"\n\nHearing the sage's instruction, the king returned to his palace. When the proper day arrived, the king, his wife, his children, and his servants observed that Ekadashi with care. The merit produced by the vow was offered to the king's father, who was then delivered and attained the heavenly realm, blessing his son.\n\nLord Krishna concluded: \"O king, one who properly observes Mokshada Ekadashi becomes free from the reactions of past sins.\" This Ekadashi is also remembered as the sacred day on which Lord Krishna spoke the Bhagavad-gita to Arjuna at Kurukshetra, opening the path of liberation for all souls."
