        "full_description": "Ekadashi, September 22, 2026\n\nThe glories of Parshva Ekadashi, which is also known as Parivartini Ekadashi or Vamana Ekadashi, are described in the Brahma Vaivarta Purana in a conversation between Lord Krishna and Maharaja Yudhishthira.\n\nMaharaja Yudhishthira asked Lord Krishna: “What is the name of the Ekadashi that falls during the waxing moon in the month of August/September? How should this Ekadashi be observed, and what benefit can be obtained by observing it? Please tell me about this in detail.”\n\nLord Krishna replied: “O king! The Ekadashi that occurs during the waxing moon in the month of August/September is called Parshva Ekadashi. This Ekadashi is very auspicious; it bestows liberation and destroys all sins. By hearing the glories of this Ekadashi, the reactions to all sinful activities are destroyed. The merit attained by observing this Ekadashi cannot be attained even by performing the Vajapeya sacrifice. This Ekadashi is also known as Jayanti. One who worships Lord Vamanadeva with devotion on this day himself becomes an object of worship for the inhabitants of the three worlds. A person who worships lotus-eyed Lord Vishnu by offering Him lotus flowers certainly returns to the abode of the Lord. On this Ekadashi, the sleeping Lord turns from His left side onto His right. That is why this Ekadashi is known as Parshva Parivartini, literally, ‘turning from one side to the other,’ Ekadashi.”\n\nMaharaja Yudhishthira said: “O Janardana! Although I have heard Your description, I still have doubts. O Lord of lords! How do You sleep, and how do You turn over? What procedures must be followed during Chaturmasya? What should people do while You sleep? Why did You bind Bali Maharaja with ropes? O my Lord! Please give me a detailed answer and remove my doubts.”\n\nLord Krishna replied: “O lion-like king! In Treta-yuga there lived a great devotee named Bali. Although born in a demonic family, he regularly worshiped Me and offered various prayers. He also worshiped the brahmanas and performed various sacrifices. Soon he gained such power that he defeated Indra, the king of heaven, and seized the heavenly kingdom.\n\nThen Indra, together with the other demigods and sages, approached Me. Hearing their prayer, I assumed the form of a dwarf, Vamana, and appeared at the sacrificial arena of King Bali dressed as a young brahmachari. I asked Bali to give Me as much land as could be measured by three steps. Hearing My request for only three steps of land, Bali asked whether I desired something more, but I showed My determination to accept only this. Without further deliberation, King Bali and his wife Vindhyavali gave Me three measures of land.”\n\nBeing the Supreme Personality of Godhead, Lord Vamanadeva gradually began to expand in size. With His first step He covered the seven lower worlds, and with His second, all the planets. Expanding further, He covered the entire sky. When Vamanadeva asked where He could place His third step, King Bali, with folded hands, offered his own head.\n\nSatisfied by his humility, I blessed him: “You will always live with Me.” On the day of this Ekadashi, which falls during the waxing moon in the month of August/September, the deity of Vamanadeva was installed in King Bali’s residence. Another form of Mine was installed upon the bed of Ananta Shesha in the Ocean of Milk.\n\nThe Supreme Lord sleeps for four months, beginning with Shayana Ekadashi and continuing until Utthana Ekadashi. During these four months, one should worship the Lord with special attention. Every Ekadashi should be properly observed. By observing this Ekadashi, one attains the result of performing one thousand horse sacrifices.”"
